cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "NIST SP 800-53 Rev 5 Control Mapping for AI Agent Decision Evidence"
message: "If you cite this mapping in standards documents, comment submissions, or academic work, please use the metadata below."
type: dataset
authors:
  - given-names: Swapan
    family-names: Shridhar
    affiliation: AgentOS
    email: swapan@getagentos.ai
repository-code: "https://github.com/getagentos/sp800-53-mapping"
url: "https://getagentos.ai"
abstract: >
  A control-by-control mapping between NIST Special Publication 800-53
  Revision 5 and a cryptographic decision evidence artifact format for
  AI agent systems. Primary mapping covers the AU (Audit and Accountability)
  family, including AU-10 Non-repudiation enhancements (1), (2), (3),
  and (5); AU-9 Hardware Write-Once Media and Cryptographic Protection;
  and AU-12 Audit Record Generation enhancements. Secondary mappings
  cover AC, IA, SR, and SI control families.
keywords:
  - NIST
  - SP 800-53
  - AI agents
  - agentic AI
  - non-repudiation
  - audit evidence
  - cryptographic attestation
  - chain of custody
  - FIPS 186-5
  - RFC 3161
  - SCITT
  - RATS
license: Apache-2.0
version: 1.0.0
date-released: 2026-05-20
